---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy · Codeflare"
  description="Privacy policy for codeflare.ch: what the contact form collects, how it is processed, and what is never stored."
  canonical="https://codeflare.ch/landing/privacy/"
>
  <Header variant="login" />

  <main>
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Privacy</h1>
      <p>
        This site is the public face of Codeflare. It sets no cookies, runs no analytics, and makes
        no third-party requests, with one exception described below.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact form</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit the contact form, the data you enter (name, email address, optional company
        name, topic, and message) together with your IP address is relayed <strong>as an email</strong>
        to the Codeflare team and used solely to respond to your inquiry. Submissions are
        <strong>not stored</strong> by this site: no database, no log of message contents. The email
        itself is retained like ordinary business correspondence.
      </p>

      <h2>Cloudflare Turnstile</h2>
      <p>
        The contact form is protected against abuse by Cloudflare Turnstile, which is loaded only on
        this site and processes connection data (including your IP address) to distinguish humans
        from bots. See Cloudflare's privacy documentation for details on Turnstile processing.
      </p>

      <h2>Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This site is served by Cloudflare infrastructure, which processes technical connection data
        (such as IP addresses) to deliver and protect the service.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>For any privacy question or request, use the contact form on the home page.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
